properties.abstract: The Rhaeto-Romanic word „surselva“, which denotes the broad valley between Disentis and Ilanz, means «above the forests». With its 2897 m Piz Muraun is definitely above the timber line. The view to Surselva and as far as the Tödi range is unobstructed. To reach this magnificent viewpoint, some entertaining scrambling is needed. It is best to undertake the descent via Garvera ridge, as it offers impressive views as well.
properties.subtitle: Above the woods
properties.title: North-south traverse from Curaglia

segments.description: From Curaglia ascend to Soliva on a marked hiking trail. From there follow the alp access road to Funtauna Rodunda (shortcuts possible). Now continue to Alp Soliva on a hiking trail to reach Garvera ridge.
segments.title: Curaglia - Soliva – Carvera ridge

segments.description: From the highest point of Garvera ridge (2384 m) follow the faint path on the north ridge of Piz Muraun (sometimes slightly off the ridge line) to the summit. On a gentle block ridge and across some rocky humps you easily reach Fuorcla da Vallesa.
segments.title: Carvera ridge - Piz Muraun - Fuorcla da Vallesa

segments.description: From Fuorcla da Vallesa follow the marked hiking trail via Pardatsch - Val Plattas (or Biscuolm, 10 Min. more) to Curaglia.
segments.title: Fuorcla da Vallesa – Curaglia
